As you can see, this file also handles the case when app runs in a so called "standalone mode", where the runtime is empty and the files need to be fetched manually. I want you to extend the build mode that has this condition:

```
(process.env.VITE_DEV_MODE || process.env.VITE_BUILD_MODE === "INLINE_ALL") &&
!process.env.VITE_STANDALONE
```
I also want the application to try and fetch the components, despite them being in the runtime. Similar to how it's done in standalone mode. When a component is found via fetch, it should override the existing (pre-built) component.